                  </hi>. I am a slater, and live in Commercial-road, Lambeth. On the 22nd of Sept. I left my son in Fleet-street, in charge of a gig, at</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184211280009"></xptr>
               <p>the end of St. Dunstan's-lane, with my son's great coat in it—on returning to the gig I found a crowd about it, and my son said a man bad taken his greftl coat—two boys came up and said they knew the man—they gave a descrip<lb></lb>tion to the policeman, and the prisoner was taken about six. weeks afterwards—the coat has not been found.</p>
